  <entry>
    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/56193</id>
    <published>2012-11-12T00:00:00+00:00</published>
    <updated>2012-11-12T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-contribution-of-basic-skills-to-health-related-outcomes-during-adulthood-evidence-from-the-bcs70"/>
    <title>The contribution of basic skills to health related outcomes during adulthood: evidence from the BCS70</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;BIS research paper no. 91. Report on a study that used British Cohort Study 1970 (BCS70) data, on adult basic skills (at age 34) and health outcomes (at ages 34 and 38) to estimate the association of adult basic skills to changes in health. Information on highest educational qualifications in adulthood was used to explore the relationship between adult basic skills and changes in health. Also included important childhood factors to look at how these factors related to the formation of basic skills in adulthood and adult health.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/55983</id>
    <published>2012-11-12T00:00:00+00:00</published>
    <updated>2012-11-12T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/valuing-adult-learning-comparing-wellbeing-valuation-and-contingent-valuation"/>
    <title>Valuing adult learning: comparing wellbeing valuation and contingent valuation</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;BIS research paper no.85. Report that uses data from the British Household Panel Survey to assess how the benefits of adult learning for society and for those who receive it. Economists think about individual benefits in terms of changes in utility and money, to compare the costs of adult learning with its benefits. Explores both experienced utility, where adult learning makes people think and feel better about life, and decision utility, adult learning is something people desire, and compares the results generated by each.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
